// SIDHKOFED CMS — Prisma schema (Phase 1).
//
// FOUNDATION SCOPE: datasource + generator + the self-contained governance `Setting`
// table only. No content/business models (events, documents, programmes, toolkits,
// media, dashboard, …) are defined yet — that is intentional. They are added module
// by module per the dependency graph (docs/foundation/03-module-dependency-graph.md).
//
// `Setting` is included verbatim from the approved schema (database-schema-design.md
// Part 13). It is the one infrastructure table the foundation needs: it has no
// foreign-key graph or enums, so it lets `prisma generate` produce a client without
// pulling in business entities, and backs the typed `settings` config surface.
// (AuditLog is deliberately NOT added yet — it relates to `users`, which would pull
// in the identity graph; the audit foundation logs structurally until then.)
//
// Conventions (docs/foundation/04-coding-standards.md §3) for when models are added:
//   - Model names PascalCase + @@map("snake_case"); fields camelCase + @map("snake_case").
//   - UUID primary keys; explicit @db.Uuid foreign keys; Decimal for money/quantities.
//   - onDelete is part of the contract: Restrict (masters/linked), Cascade (junction
//     children), SetNull (optional refs). Do not change without a reviewed migration.
//
// NOTE ON THE EXISTING FTS MIGRATION:
//   prisma/migrations/20260624154500_metadata_full_text_search adds metadata
//   `search_vector` columns + GIN indexes to content tables. It is hand-written raw
//   SQL and MUST run AFTER the base migration that creates those content tables.
//   Do not `migrate deploy` it against a fresh database until the content models and
//   their migration exist. The foundation verifies DB connectivity with `SELECT 1`,
//   which needs no tables.

generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client-js"
}

datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}

// ─────────────── Governance: Settings ───────────────
// Schema-backed key/value config (site/footer/social/translation, enquiry recipient,
// upload restrictions). Editable by Super Admin via /admin/settings; the env layer
// provides bootstrap defaults/secrets (docs/foundation/05-environment-variables.md).
model Setting {
  id          String   @id @default(uuid()) @db.Uuid
  key         String   @unique
  valueText   String?  @map("value_text")
  valueJson   Json?    @map("value_json")
  description String?
  updatedById String?  @map("updated_by") @db.Uuid
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt @map("updated_at")

  @@map("settings")
}
